definition[0]_en: A content type that consists of cartographic content expressed through a digitally encoded dataset intended to be processed by a computer.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A content type that consists of cartographic content expressed through a digitally encoded dataset intended to be processed by a computer.
scope note[0]_en: A cartographic dataset excludes cartographic data intended to be perceived in the form of an image or three-dimensional form.

definition[0]_en: A content type that consists of cartographic content expressed through line, shape, shading, etc., intended to be perceived visually as a still image or images in two dimensions.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A content type that consists of cartographic content expressed through line, shape, shading, etc., intended to be perceived visually as a still image or images in two dimensions.
scope note[0]_en: Maps, views, atlases, remote-sensing images, etc., are included.

definition[0]_en: A content type that consists of cartographic content expressed through images intended to be perceived as moving, in two dimensions.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A content type that consists of cartographic content expressed through images intended to be perceived as moving, in two dimensions.
scope note[0]_en: Satellite images of the earth or other celestial bodies in motion are included.

definition[0]_en: A content type that consists of cartographic content expressed through line, shape, and/or other forms, intended to be perceived through touch as a still image in two dimensions.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A content type that consists of cartographic content expressed through line, shape, and/or other forms, intended to be perceived through touch as a still image in two dimensions.

definition[0]_en: A content type that consists of cartographic content expressed through a form or forms intended to be perceived through touch as a three-dimensional form or forms.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A content type that consists of cartographic content expressed through a form or forms intended to be perceived through touch as a three-dimensional form or forms.

definition[0]_en: A content type that consists of cartographic content expressed through a form or forms intended to be perceived visually in three-dimensions.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A content type that consists of cartographic content expressed through a form or forms intended to be perceived visually in three-dimensions.
scope note[0]_en: Globes, relief models, etc., are included.

definition[0]_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through a digitally encoded dataset intended to be processed by a computer.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through a digitally encoded dataset intended to be processed by a computer.
scope note[0]_en: Numeric data, environmental data, etc., used by applications software to calculate averages, correlations, etc., or to produce models, etc., but not normally displayed in its raw form, are included. Excludes data intended to be perceived visually in the form of notation, image, or three-dimensional form.
scope note[1]_en: For data intended to be perceived in an audible form, see performed music, sounds, and spoken word.
scope note[2]_en: For cartographic data, see cartographic dataset.

definition[0]_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through digitally encoded instructions intended to be processed and performed by a computer.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through digitally encoded instructions intended to be processed and performed by a computer.
scope note[0]_en: Operating systems, applications software, etc., are included.

definition[0]_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through a form of notation for movement intended to be perceived visually.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through a form of notation for movement intended to be perceived visually.
scope note[0]_en: All forms of movement notation other than those intended to be perceived through touch are included.

definition[0]_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through a form of musical notation intended to be perceived visually.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through a form of musical notation intended to be perceived visually.
scope note[0]_en: All forms of music notation other than those intended to be perceived through touch are included.

definition[0]_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through music in an audible form.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through music in an audible form.
scope note[0]_en: Recorded performances of music, computer-generated music, etc., are included.

definition[0]_en: A content type that consists of content other than language or music, expressed in an audible form.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A content type that consists of content other than language or music, expressed in an audible form.
scope note[0]_en: Natural sounds, artificially produced sounds, etc., are included.

definition[0]_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through language in an audible form.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through language in an audible form.
scope note[0]_en: Recorded readings, recitations, speeches, interviews, oral histories, etc., computer-generated speech, etc., are included.

definition[0]_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through line, shape, shading, etc., intended to be perceived visually as a still image or images in two dimensions.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through line, shape, shading, etc., intended to be perceived visually as a still image or images in two dimensions.
scope note[0]_en: Drawings, paintings, diagrams, photographic images known as stills, etc., are included.
scope note[1]_en: For cartographic content intended to be perceived as a two-dimensional image, see cartographic image.
scope note[2]_en: For images intended to be perceived through touch, see tactile image.

definition[0]_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through line, shape, and/or other forms, intended to be perceived through touch as a still image in two dimensions.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through line, shape, and/or other forms, intended to be perceived through touch as a still image in two dimensions.

definition[0]_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through a form of musical notation intended to be perceived through touch.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through a form of musical notation intended to be perceived through touch.
scope note[0]_en: Braille music and other tactile forms of musical notation are included.

definition[0]_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through a form of notation for movement intended to be perceived through touch.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through a form of notation for movement intended to be perceived through touch.

definition[0]_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through a form of notation for language intended to be perceived through touch.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through a form of notation for language intended to be perceived through touch.
scope note[0]_en: Braille text and other tactile forms of language notation are included.

definition[0]_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through a form or forms intended to be perceived through touch as a three-dimensional form or forms.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through a form or forms intended to be perceived through touch as a three-dimensional form or forms.

definition[0]_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through a form of notation for language intended to be perceived visually.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through a form of notation for language intended to be perceived visually.
scope note[0]_en: All forms of language notation other than those intended to be perceived through touch are included.

definition[0]_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through a form or forms intended to be perceived visually in three-dimensions.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through a form or forms intended to be perceived visually in three-dimensions.
scope note[0]_en: Sculptures, models, naturally occurring objects and specimens, holograms, etc., are included. Excludes cartographic content intended to be perceived as a three-dimensional form. Excludes three-dimensional forms intended to be perceived through touch.

definition[0]_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through images intended to be perceived to be moving, and in three dimensions.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through images intended to be perceived to be moving, and in three dimensions.
scope note[0]_en: Three-dimensional motion pictures using live action or animation, and stereoscopic, known as S-3D, video games, etc., are included. Three-dimensional moving images may or may not be accompanied by sound.
scope note[1]_en: Three-dimensional moving images may or may not be accompanied by sound.

definition[0]_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through images intended to be perceived to be moving, and in two dimensions.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through images intended to be perceived to be moving, and in two dimensions.
scope note[0]_en: Motion pictures using live action and/or animation, film and video recordings of performances, events, etc., other than those intended to be perceived in three dimensions, are included. Moving images may or may not be accompanied by sound.

definition[0]_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through choreography in a visual form.
ToolkitDefinition_en: A content type that consists of content expressed through choreography in a visual form.
scope note[0]_en: Includes performed dance and mime, and animated choreography.
